HEADWORD: Haffle
<hw>Haf"fle</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧f"f'l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>haften</ets> to cling, stick to, Prov. G., to stop, stammer.]</ety>
<def>To stammer; to speak unintelligibly; to prevaricate.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

